column17: Epitope
Epitope Comments
The epitope was identified based on the HLA-B35 binding motif using influenza-specific bulk CTL cultures from an HLA-B35+ donor and target cells matched for HLA-B35.
The epitope is from influenza virus matrix protein M1, peptide 58-66, with L9 substituted by a methyl group, 1,2-dimethylpropylamine,  NHCH(CH(CH3)2)CH3.
No strain is given in the reference, but the peptide sequence is from Influenza A/PR/8/34, as noted in reference 13 of the paper.
A computer scoring program based on the HLA-A2.1 peptide binding motif was used to score peptides within the influenza matrix protein for likelihood of binding to HLA-A2.1.
The sequence is found in multiple strains of Influenza A virus.

A tyrosyl residue was added to M1 57-73 in order to permit radioiodination. The actual sequence used is KGILGFVFTLTVPSERY. No strain is given in the reference. A representative Swiss-prot ID is given.
